Hello and Kia Ora!  
  
** Start your game... **

At Entain, we take pride in being a Product-led organisation, with an emphasis
on creating a fantastic customer experience. Our Product and Design team is
focused on developing and delivering products that will change the face of the
gaming and wagering industry in Australia, keeping our customers coming back
and positively engaged.

As a Product Designer, your passion for crafting desirable, detailed, and
accessible digital experiences and interactions will see you escalating our
customers' product enjoyment to the level we pride ourselves on at Entain.
With the support of cutting-edge technologies and an innovative internal team,
your ability to make an essential impact on our customers is irrefutable.

** Where and how you can work... **

We have offices in Auckland, Wellington, Darwin, Sydney, Melbourne and
Brisbane. We value a flexible work environment and support a hybrid working
model, allowing employees to spend two days a week at the office, ensuring
work-life balance and individual preferences. _ This role will be based in
Brisbane. _

** Your day-to-day... **

  * Work closely with stakeholders from other business units, including product and tech, to understand design context and collaborate within team for solutions. 
  * Manage medium-sized projects independently and use initiative to build domain expertise within our products. 
  * Develop designs based on the brief and produce prototypes and wireframes for different features. 
  * Confidently present highly detailed work and provide updates to a development team. 
  * Communicate designs with stakeholders including clear and concise handover notes and flow maps. 
  * Develop and share ideas, customer insights, and feedback to improve designs and internal design processes. 
  * Conduct user research, interpret data, and apply insights to design. 
  * Deliver solutions e.g., UI, sketches, icons, illustrations) and participate in critique process to improve design acceptance. 
  * Execute a range of relevant UX research tasks, including testing and validation of ideas, with the guide of our in house UX team. 

** You're a match if you ideally have... **

  * Demonstrated experience in a commercial environment as a Product Designer - with an emphasis on visual design. 
  * Strong Interpersonal and communication skills. 
  * Ambition to manage your workload autonomously and independently, while also taking direction. 
  * Experienced in prototyping and visual tools (e.g., Figma) and collaborative tools (Fig jam or Miro). 
  * Experience working within a design system with proven ability to take a given style and apply across a library of assets. 
  * Excellent understanding of design systems, UX and UI product design. 
  * Familiar with Native iOS & Android patterns and nuances 
  * Ability to design in a white label environment for multiple brands. 
  * An inquisitive mind paired, the desire to think critically, and the confidence to advocate your research and insights. 

** Who are we? **

At Entain Australia & New Zealand, we're on a mission to revolutionise the
world of sports and gaming venue entertainment. We're the home of Australia
and New Zealand's best gaming and tech talent, with a passion for pushing
boundaries and creating unforgettable experiences.

We have a host of leading brands under the Entain umbrella â€“ our customers can
experience the best of sports betting and entertainment with Ladbrokes
Australia and neds, where together they provide thrilling avenues for sports
enthusiasts and racing aficionados alike.

We're also proud to support racing and sport in New Zealand through our
25-year strategic partnership with TAB NZ. The TAB brand in New Zealand
connects enthusiasts to the heart of the action, whether it's horse racing,
greyhounds, or a variety of thrilling sports.

** Entain Lifestyle... **

  * Embrace your need for a work-life balance through our 9-day fortnight. 
  * Celebrate the joy of starting a family with 12 weeks of paid parental leave. 
  * Indulge in a range of wellness benefits through our wellness calendar, including, heavily subsidized gym memberships and other paid-for services. 
  * Enjoy the convenience of a free onsite barista and a fully stocked fridge and pantry, ensuring breakfast and lunch are taken care of. 
  * A wealth of learning and development opportunities, empowering you to broaden your expertise and professional growth. 
  * Company-wide events designed to honour and celebrate the outstanding achievements of our exceptional team. 
  * We LOVE Entertainment, Racing and Sports are at the heart of everything we do. So, it only makes sense that we provide access to staff giveaways to sporting and racing events. 

_ As a global employer, Entain is committed to providing a safe, fun, and
inclusive culture where our people feel like they truly belong. We are a
multicultural business that values, celebrates and respects individual
differences, so whatever your sexuality, gender, gender identity, ability,
age, race, religion, or belief, you will have a voice here, and the space to
do your best work. Our diverse internal networks provide support for you to
express your views and make a positive difference. _

